6 November 2019 The Springboks will kick off their 'Champions Tour' which is a country-wide bus tour with the Webb Ellis Cup in the country on Thursday, November 7. The tour will begin with the Gauteng province, in Pretoria, Johannesburg and Soweto. Thereafter, the tour will visit Durban (Friday, November 8), East London (Saturday, November 9), Port Elizabeth (Sunday, November 10) and concludes in Cape Town on Monday, November 11. The bus routes are as follows: Pretoria, Thursday, November 7 (10:00-11:00) Johannesburg, Thursday, November 7 (13:30-14:15) Soweto, Thursday, November 7 (15:00-16:00) Durban, Friday, November 8 (10:00-12:00) East London, Saturday, November 9 (10:00-14:00) Port Elizabeth, Sunday, November 10 (10:00-13:00) Cape Town (CBD), Monday, November 11 (11:30-13:00) Enquiries:Phumla WilliamsCell: 083 5010 139